Rubus leucodermis is a species of shrub in the rose family.
The plant has long, thorny stems that can reach up to 2 meters in length.
Leaves are typically dark green with a slightly hairy texture and an oval shape.
The flowers are white, with 5 petals and a yellow center. They bloom in clusters from spring to early summer.
Fruits are small, round, and bright red in color, resembling a raspberry or blackberry.
Rubus leucodermis is found in various habitats, including mountain slopes, forest edges, and open meadows.
This plant is used by wildlife for food and shelter, and is also used by humans for medicinal purposes.
